Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 9 (A.A) -- Azeri President Geydar 
Aliyev, currently in Turkey on an official visit, on Wednesday 
[9 February] met with Parliament Speaker Husamettin Cindoruk. 
  Cindoruk during the meeting said that Turkey and Azerbaijan 
are brother countries expressing his belief that invading 
Armenian forces will draw back from Azeri land. 
  He said that Turkey does not intervene in other countries' 
internal affairs, but wishes for all Turkic republics to be 
democratically governed. 
  Aliyev expressed his country's wishes for further developing 
bilateral relations with Turkey, and said he is very happy and 
thankful to be at the parliament and addressing its members. 

